<br>
Ok, lvl 31, have Jboots and 200int, I should be able to take a zelniak, right? <br>
<br>
I buff up, look over the spells i have up, snare's up there, so is root. Try to summon a familiar. Fizzle, fizzle, fizzle, fizzle, fizzle, fizzle, ah, forget it. Some unidentified nukes up, seem to be of the right level so I leave them there to be tested.<br>
<br>
Ok, I'm gonna get this miniature beast of burden. Have to chase after it at crappy Jboot speed and can't snare it due to out of range issues. I decide to root it. Root breaks 2 seconds later. I run off trying to get far away enough to root it again. Damn, jboots sure is a lot slower than SoE. Finally manage to reroot it. At this point I'm at 50% hp due to starting with max 500hp. Curse lack of heal spell. <br>
<br>
Snare. Ok, at least I didn't snare myself. Run back a little more. Hmm, I wonder which nuke to use. Press random_nuke_01, 200dmg. Root break. Run back some more. Press random_nuke_02. Miscalculated distance and cast time, get hit, 30% hp, nuke goes off for 260 damage. Run back some more, try to cast random_nuke_03 get it off just as I get hit again by the mob.<br>
<br>
15% hp, at this point I'm pretty near the netherbian lair zoneline. Snare wears off. &quot;Oh shit, forgot about that short duration snare thing.&quot; Start running as fast as my Jboot powered feet will carry me. At this point a warrior sees me and either out of interest of &quot;saving&quot; me or KSing, kills it for me. <br>
<br>
So, there you have it, an account of a druid getting owned trying to play a wizard, for your laughing pleasure.  I think I'm gonna leave that wizard alone from now on <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
